 Here is a C++ function that converts markdown to HTML:

```cpp
std::string markdown_to_html(const std::string& markdown) {
  std::string html;

  html.reserve(markdown.size());

  // Iterate through markdown string
  for (char c : markdown) {
    if (c == '\\') {
      // If backslash, indicate start of escape sequence
      html.push_back(c);
      c = next_character(markdown, c);
    } else {
      html.push_back(c);
    }
  }

  // Apply HTML escaping
  html = html_escape(html);

  return html;
}
```

This iterates through the markdown string character by character, escaping backslashes, and then applying HTML escaping to the result. It returns the HTML formatted text.

